FPL ENERGY ILLINOIS WIND, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
FPL Energy Illinois Wind, LLC ("Lee DeKalb") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Lee DeKalb generating facility ("Lee DeKalb Facility").
The Lee DeKalb Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in DeKalb County, Illinois. The Lee DeKalb Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Commonwealth Edison Company and under the operational control of the PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Lee DeKalb's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Lee DeKalb Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Lee DeKalb's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Lee DeKalb shall be subject to Schedule 2 of PJM's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $990,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $82,500.00.
